  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM10.6.10">
<l>niṉṟār mukappuc ciṟitum niṉaiyāṉ vayiṟṟai niṟaippā ṉuṟippāl tayirney</l>
<l>aṉṟāyc ciyarveṇ ṇeyviḻuṅ kiyura loṭāppuṇ  ṭirunta perumā ṉaṭimēl</l>
<l>naṉṟā yatolcīr vayalmaṅ kaiyarkōṉ kaliya ṉolicey tamiḻmā laivallār</l>
<l>eṉṟā ṉumeytā riṭariṉ pameyti yimaiyōrk kumappāl celavey tuvārē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master the Tamil garland created with the words of Kaliyaṉ,</l>
<l rend="indent">king of those of Maṅkai with good, ancient, and prosperous fields,</l>
<l>At the feet of the great lord who was tied to a churning rod</l>
<l rend="indent">having gulped down the  butter, net[-hung] milk, curds,</l>
<l rend="indent">and ghee of the herder women that day</l>
<l>So that his stomach was full, that one who did not think for even a bit</l>
<l rend="indent">of those standing [right] before him,</l>
<l>They will never attain sorrows; attaining delight, they will get to go beyond</l>
<l rend="indent">the unblinking [celestials].</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
